A 22-year-old Colorado man believed he would die while being swept up in an avalanche and almost completely buried while skiing out of bounds in Vail.

Edwin LaMair was on an off-track expedition with his brother and friend on Sunday about 4.30pm on top of Vail Mountain when he ventured off alone.

Suddenly LaMair found himself swallowed by snow and fearing the worst.

'I definitely thought I might die while I was sliding,' he told Fox News.

