'I knew if I got buried it was going to be a very bad situation.

'I couldn't move at all. It was basically like I was being buried in sand.'

Luckily LaMair's brother, who had a camera mounted to his helmet, was able to find him and quickly started digging him out using his hands.

Ski patrol was called but didn't respond.

'I was just so grateful to be above the surface a little bit,' LaMair said.

'I think it would have been a lot more traumatic if I had been completely buried.'

